The ''Earthzone''-class shuttle is a popular ship design built at the [[Freeworlds Shipyard]].

Although the basic design in unarmed, [[Anarchist]] groups often start with the frame and add weapons and armor.

{{TEC}}

Enhanced humans have minor, germ-line genetic modifications that allow them to adapt to particular environments. For example, spacers have enhanced lungs that can survive a greater concentration of carbon dioxide than pure humans.
== See Also == * [[Human augmentations & enhancements]]
{{TEC}}

Etherium is a rare ore with mysterious properties.

Crystals of etherium are used to generate energy fields, such as those produced by shield generators.

{{TEC}}

Almost nothing is known about Ferian miners, since they avoid all human contact. They are believed to be [[zoanthropes]] who devote themselves to a simple existence as asteroid miners.
Ferians are known to trade with [[Ringers]] and (possibly) [[Teratons]].
[[Category:Sovereign]] {{TEC}}

Field crystals are used to moderate and sustain the force fields produced by shield generators.

The kind of field crystal used affects the properties of the force field. For example, yellow etherium field crystals create force fields that reflect positron energy.

{{TEC}}

Fission reactors work by splitting the nuclei of heavy atoms such as [[uranium]] and [[plutonium]]. The process generates heat (which can be converted to electricity).

Fission reactors, invented in the twentieth century, are still used in small stations and backwards worlds.

{{TEC}}

Fusion reactors generate energy by fusing light atoms such as hydrogen and helium to generate heat (which can be converted to electricity).

Fusion power is still the most common source of power in [[Human Space]]. Almost all non-military stations and starships use a fusion reactor.

{{TEC}}

A generi is a unit of Galactic time defined to be one-thousandth of an [[arc]]. A generi is roughly 45 years.
== See Also == * [[Galactic timeline]]
{{TEC}}

Heliotropes are members of a quasi-religious organization founded on principles opposing entropy and energy-death. They gather in colonies in the inner part of a star system, collecting solar energy and converting it to high-density fuel.
Heliotropes are generally hostile to all other human groups, whom they consider inferior and unworthy of the gift of energy.
[[Category:Sovereign]] {{TEC}}

In exobiological taxonomy the domain is the highest rank of lifeforms. All living organisms in the Galaxy (including humans) belong to one of these domains:
* [[Carbosilicate (domain)|Carbosilicate]]: rock and crystalline creatures. * [[Ferroelectric (domain)|Ferroelectric]]: cybernetic and metallic lifeforms. * [[Hydrogenia (domain)|Hydrogenia]]: large, gas giant inhabitants. * [[Monomorphia]]: massive single organisms similar to fungi. * [[Nebular (domain)|Nebular]]: rarefied beings consisting of interacting dust motes in nebulae. * [[Neutronia]]: hyperdense organisms living on white dwarfs and neutron stars. * [[Oxygenia]]: carbon-based, oxygen breathers, human-scale. * [[Photosynthic]]: photosynthetic life. * [[Transcendent (domain)|Transcendent]]: non-baryonic lifeforms like Domina and Oracus.
{{TEC}}

Outlaws in [[Human Space]] run a black market that trades in illegal items and services.
== See Also == * [[Black Market (reference)]]
{{TEC}}

With all the shipping of goods and information across [[Human Space]] there is a lucrative opportunity for piracy. The Charon Pirates started out raiding the Earth-Titan run during the twenty-second century, but now they are spread throughout many star systems (even some non-Human ones). The Charon Pirates are loosely organized; individual groups have a high degree of autonomy but pay a tribute to the larger organization.
The Charon Pirates have been using [[United African Ships]] bought on the surplus market.
[[Category:Sovereign]] {{TEC}}

The Freeworld Anarchist Movement is a fanatical group that seeks to disrupt and destroy the [[Corporate Hierarchy]]. Anarchists groups are aggressive and somewhat sophisticated technologically, but their numbers are few and the Corporate Hierarchy does not (currently) consider them to be a strategic threat.

